Pearl Louie Brandt is Winnie's daughter. Pearl is the child of Chinese immigrants and is a person who is caught between her American self and her Chinese ancestry and parents. She is married to an American man and feels more American than she does Chinese. She, like her mother, harbor's secrets, and she has not told her mother, when the novel opens, about her multiple sclerosis.Read anin-depth analysis of Pearl Louie Brandt.